      "date": "2012-05-17 05:08:18.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nThis check is only needed for kernels _older_ than 2.6.18, so this patch shouldn't be landing to master (where we are actively removing support for kernels < 2.6.18).\n\nI verified in upstream kernel git that the change to 5-arg get_sb() was present in vanilla 2.6.18, and exists all the way to 2.6.38.  In 2.6.39 the get_sb() method disappears completely, and is replaced with \"->mount()\", but that is something to fix once we port to a newer kernel.  There may already be patches for this in Gerrit, since people are already working on 3.1 and 3.3 kernel support.\n\nI think this patch should be abandoned.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
