          "date": "2012-05-16 08:07:09.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-1411 obdclass: compatibility for kernels < 2.6.18",
        "message": "LU-1411 obdclass: compatibility for kernels < 2.6.18\n\nlustre_get_sb() conditionally calls get_sb_nodev() with a struct\nlustre_mount_data2 * for kernels 2.6.18 and newer, and a void * data\npointer for older kernels.  However, lustre_fill_super()\nunconditionally casts its void *data argument to a struct\nlustre_mount_data2 *, which causes a crash when we deference into it\non older kenels. To fix this, add conditional code to support older\nkernels.\n\nChange-Id: Ic47e25bc70008fe44596e98858c4b422cbd23046\nSigned-off-by: Bobi Jam <bobijam@whamcloud.com>\nSigned-off-by: Ned Bass <bass6@llnl.gov>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
